@aud - Most teas are a type of PEKOE or orange PEKOE. All PEKOE means is that the tea is composed of the young leaves. And "orange PEKOE" means slightly older leaves. 

ASSAM, Darjeeling, Keemun, etc. etc, can all be made from PEKOE leaves. 

There is no citrus in orange PEKOE. It's a type of tea leaf.

